{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Review the PIP assessment process to make it fairer for people with epilepsy",
        "additional_details": "Of those who previously received DLA, 54% were denied PIP, this is the second highest rejection rate out of all health conditions and double the national average. Additionally, 65% of new claims for PIP were denied the benefit. However, of the third that appealed the decision 78% were granted PIP. This is evidence that a review must be undertaken into how people with epilepsy are assessed for PIP to make the system fairer.",
        "background": "People with epilepsy are disproportionately discriminated against during the Personal Independence Payment (PIP) assessment process.",
